          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search               This article does not cite any sources. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. (January 2007) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)     Hourglass      Studio album by Kate Rusby   Released 1 March 1997   Genre English folk   Length 46:48   Label Pure Records   Producer John McCusker   Kate Rusby chronology       Hourglass (1997) Sleepless (1999)      Hourglass is the debut studio album by English contermporary folk musician Kate Rusby, released on March 1, 1997, on Pure Records. Track listing[edit]  "Sir Eglamore" (Traditional; Rusby) "As I Roved Out" (Traditional) "Jolly Ploughboys" (Traditional) "Annan Waters" (Traditional) "Stananivy" (McCusker, Rusby) - "Jack and Jill" (Rusby; Traditional) "A Rose in April" (Rusby) "Radio Sweetheart" (Miller, McCusker) "I Am Stretched on Your Grave" (Frank O'Connor, Rusby) "Old Man Time" (Rusby) "Drowned Lovers" (Traditional) "Bold Riley" (Traditional)  Personnel[edit] Produced by John McCusker Engineered by Moray Munro Recorded at Temple Record Studio, Midlothian, Scotland Mastered by Andy Seward Kate Rusby : vocals, piano, guitar (3, 6, 9) Ian Carr: guitar (1, 5, 7, 10) Andy Cutting : diatonic accordion Donald Hay : percussion Conrad Ivitsky : double bass Alison Kinnaird : cello John McCusker : fiddles Michael McGoldrick : flute, whistles Tony McManus : guitar (2, 8) Alan Reid : harmony vocals (4) Eric Rigler : uilleann pipes Davy Steele : harmony vocals (3, 11) All tracks arranged by Kate Rusby and John McCusker (Additional arrangement by Ian Carr on tracks 1, 4, 7, 10)         v t e   Kate Rusby          Discography         Studio albums    Hourglass Sleepless Little Lights Underneath the Stars The Girl Who Couldn't Fly Awkward Annie Make the Light Ghost         Christmas albums    Sweet Bells While Mortals Sleep The Frost Is All Over         Anniversary albums    10 20         Other albums    Heartlands         DVDs    Live From Leeds Live at Christmas         Other    Jam & Jerusalem Heartlands (film) Kathryn Roberts The Poozies             This 1990s folk album-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Hourglass_(Kate_Rusby_album)&oldid=653196205"          Categories: Kate Rusby albums1997 debut albums1990s folk album stubsHidden categories: Articles lacking sources from January 2007All articles lacking sourcesArticles with hAudio microformatsAll stub articles            
